The Macedonian people voted Sunday on whether to change their country's name to "Republic of North Macedonia", a move that would resolve a decades-old dispute with Greece, which has blocked Macedonia's attempts to gain membership of the EU and NATO.
Greece has a province named Macedonia and maintains that the name of their northern neighbour constitutes a claim on Greek territory, and has therefore used their veto power when Macedonia has applied to join NATO and the EU.
